Compute simple slopes

Compute simple slopes.

\[ \begin{align} \widehat{salary} &= \beta_0 + (\beta_1 \cdot service) + (\beta_2 \cdot dept) \\ \widehat{salary} &= 28.7 + (4.4 \cdot service) + (-19.7 \cdot dept) \\ \end{align} \]

When \(dept = 0\) (Accounts):

\[ \begin{align} \widehat{salary}_{acct} &= 28.7 + (4.4 \cdot service) + (-19.7 \cdot 0) \\ \widehat{salary}_{acct} &= 28.7 + (4.4 \cdot service) \\ \end{align} \] When \(dept = 1\) (Managers):

\[ \begin{align} \widehat{salary}_{mng} &= 28.7 + (4.4 \cdot service) + (-19.7 \cdot 1) \\ \widehat{salary}_{mng} &= 28.7 - 19.7 + (4.4 \cdot service) \\ \widehat{salary}_{mng} &= 9 + (4.4 \cdot service) \\ \end{align} \]

Model: with interaction

Compute simple slopes

By hand

\[ \begin{align} \widehat{salary} &= \beta_0 + (\beta_1 \cdot serv) + (\beta_2 \cdot dept) + (\beta_3 \cdot serv \cdot dept)\\ \widehat{salary} &= 21.4 + (5.8 \cdot serv) + (-4.5 \cdot dept) + (-3.1 \cdot serv \cdot dept)\\ \end{align} \]

When \(dept = 0\) (Accounts):

\[ \begin{align} \widehat{salary}_{acct} &= 21.4 + (5.8 \cdot serv) + (-4.5 \cdot dept) + (-3.1 \cdot serv \cdot dept)\\ \widehat{salary}_{acct} &= 21.4 + (5.8 \cdot serv) + (-4.5 \cdot 0) + (-3.1 \cdot serv \cdot 0)\\ \widehat{salary}_{acct} &= 21.4 + (5.8 \cdot serv)\\ \end{align} \]

When \(dept = 1\) (Managers):

\[ \begin{align} \widehat{salary}_{mng} &= 21.4 + (5.8 \cdot serv) + (-4.5 \cdot dept) + (-3.1 \cdot serv \cdot dept)\\ \widehat{salary}_{mng} &= 21.4 + (5.8 \cdot serv) + (-4.5 \cdot 1) + (-3.1 \cdot serv \cdot 1)\\ \widehat{salary}_{mng} &= 21.4 -4.5 + (5.8 \cdot serv) + (-3.1 \cdot serv)\\ \widehat{salary}_{mng} &= 16.9 + (5.8 \cdot serv) + (-3.1 \cdot serv)\\ \widehat{salary}_{mng} &= 16.9 + ((5.8 - 3.1) \cdot serv) \\ \widehat{salary}_{mng} &= 16.9 + (2.7 \cdot serv)\\ \end{align} \]

in R

When dept = 0 (acct):

coef(m2)[['(Intercept)']]  # intercept
coef(m2)[['service']]      # slope

When dept = 1 (mng)

coef(m2)[['(Intercept)']] + coef(m2)[['deptManagers']]      # intercept
coef(m2)[['service']] + coef(m2)[['service:deptManagers']]  # slope

Asis y-intercept plot

m2_simple_effs <- tibble(
  dept = c('Accounts', 'Managers'),
  modx_group = c('Accounts', 'Managers'),
  int = c(21.4, 16.9),
  slp = c(5.8, 2.7)
)

plot_m2_probe_intercept <- plot_m2_probe
plot_m2_probe_intercept$layers[[1]] <- NULL

plot_m2_probe_intercept +
  xlim(-7, 7) +
  ylim(10, 75) +
  geom_abline(
    data = m2_simple_effs, 
    aes(intercept = int, slope = slp, colour = dept, linetype = dept),
    linewidth = 1.5
  ) +
  geom_point(
    data = m2_simple_effs,
    x = 0,
    aes(y = int),
    size = 5,
    shape = 15
  ) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, linetype = 'dotted') +
  labs(
    subtitle = 'service as-is'
  ) +
  theme(
    legend.position = 'bottom'
  ) +
  NULL

Plot min-shifted predictor.

salary <- salary |>
  mutate(
    service_min = service - min(service)
  )

salary |>
  ggplot(aes(x = service_min, y = salary)) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, colour = 'red', linewidth = 2) +
  geom_point() +
  NULL
